title: FAA reduces airspace restrictions for Cape Canaveral launches
summary: The FAA has started to reduce the amount of airspace it closes for launches from Cape Canaveral as part of efforts to limit the impact of growing launch activity on commercial aviation.

title: Indian SSA startup raises $10 million
summary: An Indian startup has raised $10 million to start development of commercial space situational awareness (SSA) capabilities that will include data from spacecraft.

title: Vyoma raises $9 million for debris-monitoring satellites
summary: German startup Vyoma said June 20 it has raised 8.5 million euros ($9.3 million) to develop space debris-monitoring satellites from investors that include French aerospace giant Safran, which will help develop the constellation.

title: United Launch Alliance ready for penultimate Delta IV Heavy launch
summary: United Launch Alliance is targeting the launch of the penultimate Delta IV Heavy with the secretive NROL-68 mission at 3:29 AM ET...

title: ULA’s penultimate Delta IV Heavy to launch with NROL-68 mission
summary: United Launch Alliance’s penultimate Delta IV Heavy rocket will take flight on the NROL-68 mission Wednesday, lofting a secretive payload for the National Reconnaissance Office. Liftoff, from Space Launch Complex 37B at Cape Canaveral, is expected at 3:29 AM EDT (07:29 UTC).

title: After tough start this year, United Launch Alliance can turn things around tonight

title: NASA Plans Coverage of Roscosmos Spacewalk Outside Space Station
summary: NASA will provide live coverage as two Roscosmos cosmonauts conduct a spacewalk outside the International Space Station Thursday, June 22, for station upgrades and retrieval of equipment.

title: Intelsat orders another servicing mission from Northrop Grumman’s SpaceLogistics
summary: SpaceLogistics announced June 20 it has three confirmed orders for its refueling pods that will fly to orbit on a servicing mission in early 2025.

title: True Anomaly to pursue military contracts for virtual, live training tech
summary: True Anomaly announced plans to provide digital and live training ranges as a service.
